Add Hosting Only Domain

If you are adding a .uk domain for transfer please read the How to transfer a .uk domain to Porkbun knowledge base article before continuing.

A Hosting Only domain is a domain name that uses one or more Porkbun hosting products (web hosting, URL forwarding, DNS hosting, email, Domain Marketplace, etc.) even though the domain is still registered at a different registrar.

In order to use Porkbun hosting, the domain must be configured with our default nameservers. Please assign these nameservers at your current registrar as soon as possible:

  • maceio.porkbun.com
  • salvador.porkbun.com
  • fortaleza.porkbun.com
  • curitiba.porkbun.com

If you can't assign our nameservers quite yet, you can still add the domain to Domain Management, we'll provide additional instructions after you click Submit.


DNS Ownership Verification

You can verify ownership of the domain by configuring the following DNS record on the domain's current nameservers. Once the record has been configured, click the submit button.

Type: TXT
Hostname: bun-verify.
Answer:


A domain name you control, registered at another registrar.

Additional Registration Requirements

.ai domain names uniquely require registration and renewal periods of at least two years. This means that when you register a .ai domain there's a two year minimum. If you have auto-renew turned on, the domain will renew for two years instead of one as it nears expiration.
